longBusinessSummary: HTC Purenergy Inc., doing business as HTC Extraction Systems, develops, aggregates, and commercializes proprietary technologies relating to gas, liquid and biomass extraction, distillation, purification, and reclamation in Canada. It operates through two segments, HTC's Delta CleanTech Division and HTC's Hemp Division. The HTC's Delta CleanTech Division provides products and services related to clean energy industries. The HTC's Hemp Division engages in hemp-based activities, such as hemp extraction, refining, formulation, and distribution in the State of California. The company's products include Delta purification systems/ CO2 capture systems, Delta reclaimer systems, and hydrogen thermochem systems. The company was formerly known as HTC Hydrogen Technologies Corp. and changed its name to HTC Purenergy Inc. in February 2008. HTC Purenergy Inc. is headquartered in Regina, Canada.
